  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Promotion of Durable Solutions in Darfur, South Kordofan and Blue Nile</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">To promote durable solutions in Sudan, IOM is using a flexible, multi-sectoral and community-based approach that focuses on addressing identified humanitarian and early recovery needs of the most vulnerable affected communities in selected localities, such as female headed households, persons with disabilities and elderly. Building on its extensive operational footprint across all five states in Darfur, South Kordofan, East Sudan, Blue Nile and Abyei and institutional experience in supporting durable solutions in displacement affected contexts, IOM is focuses on providing life-saving services, improving levels of stability and promoting durable solutions for vulnerable internally displaced persons and returnees in all five states in Darfur, Blue Nile and South Kordofan.</narrative>
  </description>
